The paper proposes an automated method for detecting lacunes of presumed vascular origin using deep convolutional neural networks. This involves image analysis and machine learning, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential benefits of the proposed method for human observers, indicating a possible interest in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
